metadata.name: REIN #2
metadata.description:
REIN

A generative approach to personal interpretation of reincarnation

It is not my right and job to prove the existence of reincarnation, but the concept makes a good dialogue for my heart and also is a fun challenge for my brain.

1. About the role:

The element on the screen is basically the metaphor for every object/person in your current life.

As the ACTOR, you can make choice under your instant willingness and travel in this world with limited time.

As the OBSERVER you can watch the above and question and dialogue with the ACTOR and alter its choice.

2. About the visualizations:

In order to present our big world in a limited 2D graphical approach. I shrink the dimensions and the detail of the existing reality.

Humans and Objects are dots, 3D entities like us become tiny dots (zero dimension) on a 3D space where their activity is backward translated to 2D perspective coordinates

Interactions between two entities are lines, and in our world planes or shapes were formed when interactions involved multiple people or objects. Which becomes an event.

We now as observer from the higher ground can witness the events‚Äô change, progress, and karma by the continuous growth of the plane into various shapes.

Every world we reincarnated back into will have a visual color and an audio color tone. It is considered to be the theme of that particular life.

The final composition becomes a mix of the above, everything is merely the same but everything yet looks different. Depends on your perspective."

3. Some personal sharing thru creating REIN:

Life is short - I am happy if you are feeling annoyed and you feel the screen comes and fades so fast. Indeed this is my personal feeling about life, too short and things ended before you realize it.

Some life is super long and boring - I am also happy if you felt so. So sing and discover your song of life when you are in the room. It happens once only with this combination.

No time to prepare/predict/prejudge - but you can enjoy cause you/he/she/it/they/we will end in here suddenly. So enjoy the up and down, sweet and sour of every bit.

There is always an intangible target and goal preset to you, and it cast a line between you and it. You can choose to ignore it or be actively chasing it. But no matter which choices you made, your locus was left and shown in front of your eyes.

4. Observer‚Äôs responsibility and award
This work inspires me that in life we can both be the actors/actress and also the observer.

What matters more to you?
The background, your choice, or both?
Are you the observer guy who sits and doesn‚Äôt move?
Are you moving towards the [goal] linking with you? Do you keep chasing it?
Are you caring about the background more? Do you have a feeling they somehow related to you?
Or do you simply move your life freely without caring about the other happening?
Your voice is too loud or not?
Will you find the background noise too loud?
What can you do with it?
If the target connected to you is hollow and empty, would you still care about it?

And Why? Why do you feel so?
Which part of the above dialogue is related to your existing life?
What can we do/change/keep?
What you really can control?"


// [Click] - The sound of the work can be muted by clicking again the screen
// [s] - Take a selfie of this world and you inside
// [spacebar] - you can stop the time and walk/think freely like NEO in the matrix

Behind [REIN]
As a generative artist, I force myself to seek the possible ways to use these tools/skills/presentation forms.

In Traveler, it is about finding the difference between being alone and feeling loneliness
In FEA, it is about possibilities
In BULLET, it is about courage and faith
In REIN, I hope we can treasure what we lost and gained.

Art to me can be the visualization of aesthetics or a mutually enjoyable creative process for you and me.

Or like this time in REIN.

A journey towards our room inside our heart shape box.

metadata.name: PolyGarden #59
metadata.description:
Polygons, patterns and flowers are mixtured in my garden. I start with a birdeye view of the garden and its geometric structure. The species diversity and the random stack of rocks, sands, fences and other objects are main structures I want to capture, in an abstract and planar style. 

Moreover, in this project, I also try to explore the representation ability of generative art. I select three elements: shape of entity, layout of palette, and stack of object location. The factors behind these elements are the balance of randomness and structure: the generative art generates the variants from randomness but restricts its chaos with structure (deterministic constraints) to represent the meaningful results. 

Variables:
- 4 layouts
- 6 texture patterns
- 15 color palette
- 3 randomness
- 2 completeness

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: A Watch #125
metadata.description:
Another adventure in narrated horology: this work features entirely new texts, authored by AI that I trained on a set of novels. Each minute is an AI prose output, a fragment of a novel that doesn't exist, generated from the time itself.

The form factor is ideal for smaller window sizes and displays, although it will scale to any size. With the right device, you could probably wear it on your wrist.

Nearly 5,000 unique text templates are included, many of which feature variable character names, for which I sourced approximately 1.8 million possible first names and 150,000 possible surnames from U.S. Census data: https://github.com/rossgoodwin/american-names

I wanted to provide just enough text for each minute so that you could read the whole excerpt before the minute ends, though you might need to read briskly. None of the passages have been edited manually, and some remain quite glitchy, as intended. You may recognize a few motifs or proper names here and there, depending on the books you're familiar with, but each passage remains wholly original otherwise.

Each edition features either a linear or nonlinear text sequence:

Nonlinear editions will all show one of two possible template texts for each minute, and will read like fragments from multiple (strange and glitchy) novels. Nonlinear sequences feature independently generated texts, with variable character names unique to each minute of each edition.

Linear editions will all show the same template text for each minute, and will read like (strange and glitchy) 24-hour novels. For linear sequences, I utilized a generative prompting technique in which each minute's text is generated partially from the text of the minute before it. Variable character names for linear sequences are unique to each edition and repeat throughout the day.

Aesthetic possibilities for each edition include 16 color palettes, 8 fonts, 7 depths, 5 types of numerals, and 3 types of hands. Some editions have color-accented second hands and minute marks, while others appear more static and minimalist, without any numerals or second hand at all.

This token relies on p5.js for the clockwork, vanilla JS for the text.



Double click to toggle fullscreen.

Push `d` to download current minute's text as a .txt file.

metadata.name: Daydreamer #66
metadata.description:
‚ÄòFor the artist communication with nature remains the most essential condition. The artist is human, himself nature; part of nature within natural space.‚Äô (Paul Klee, 1944) 


Working on long-form nature has an interesting side effect. On the one hand, you're attempting a shallow imitation of a landscape.... You are working with cold logic and code, vainly trying to control randomness to create this virtual facsimile, something you know is artificial.... 

....and yet.... even with all this left-brain activity, your right-brain pushes back, and imagines being there. While working on this project I found myself continually daydreaming, wandering off to hear the sounds of waterfalls, or the crunch of walking along a sandy lake shore. If you've ever wondered about coding, I urge you to learn. Daydreams await....


Press '1' once rendering is finished, to redraw at 5120x5120 resolution 
Press '2' to export without post-processing effects 

3rd party libraries (license text and links included in source) 
- p5.js - Creative coding framework 
- JS Topology Suite "JSTS", a port of Java Topology Suite "JTS" - High-level Geometry library 
- WebGLImageFilter, Dominic Szablewski - phoboslab.org 

I have tried to use soft blurs and shadows to give a sense of layering and depth to the scene. After viewing for a while, it reminds me of 3D paper-art. There are traits for colour and amount of birds, waterfalls, etc. but none are especially rare ‚Äì These properties are intended for filtering the collection.

metadata.name: Audio Visual Harmonics #24
metadata.description:
See Sound. Hear Light.

Each piece generates four unique oscillators, which in turn drive a unique visual manifestation of the sound in realtime.  Touch or click on the piece to start.

Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps realtime rendering.

metadata.name: Audio Visual Harmonics II #18
metadata.description:
TAP TO PLAY.

Extending "Audio Visual Harmonics", this piece generates a unique harmonic sequence of four oscillators.  The frequency intervals are melodic and span different musical modes. More pure interval steps are more rare.      

Visuals are entirely defined by the audio; what you see is what you hear.  

Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps realtime rendering.

metadata.description:

Visuals are entirely defined by the audio; what you see is what you hear.

Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps realtime rendering.

metadata.name: Southern Gothic #154
metadata.description:
‚ÄúSouthern Gothic‚Äù is my debut release on the fxhash platform. The project is created entirely through code. All copyrights are released to the holder of each image output, even for commercial purposes.

‚ÄúSouthern Gothic‚Äù borrows its name from the literary genre made famous by writers like Flannery O‚ÄôConnor and Carson McCullers. Rather than illustrating a singular setting, the code generates an entire rural townscape, thereby, blurring the boundaries between representation and narrative. The individual scenes are framed frontally with an intentionally flat aesthetic character, referencing traditional folk art of the American South. The absence of human figures within these scenes adds to their overwhelming sense of darkness and forlorn. Observing multiple scenes side-by-side, one may even get the strange feeling that something terrible has happened (or is about to happen) in this rural landscape.

Pressing the down arrow saves the coded output as a .png image.

metadata.description:
twofiftythousand is about the chaos of unlimited decisions. Look for a pattern in the noise.

Press 's' to save an image while in full-screen mode.

metadata.name: Puzzles of the mind #199
metadata.description:
This is abstract art based on mathematical structure.
The puzzle of your mind seems broken and rearranged.

Mode has 2 variations.
 - Normal
 - Black
Color has 3 variations.
 - Â∏∏Á£ê-tokiwa- (Green)
 - ÁúüÊú±-shinshu- (Red)
 - Á¥∫Á¢ß-konpeki- (Blue)
Color Level has 2 variations.
 - High
 - Low
Square Size has 3 variations.
 - Small
 - Middle
 - Large

Tokiwa is a Japanese word meaning always the same. It's green like the color of evergreen leaves.

Shinshu is a Japanese word that refers to a dull red color like vermilion. It means vermilion in its natural state with nothing mixed in.

Konpeki is a Japanese word that describes a deep blue, very close to azure. It's like a clear sky with summer sunshine.

Controls (in live view):
 - Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
 - Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
 - Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: Unicorn #765
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: Secret Stairways #60
metadata.description:
"Secret Stairways" is a project that uses principles of Cellular Automaton to construct buildings that can remember a castle, villages...Wich I have many inspirations in architecture and buildings from the place I live (Minas Gerais).

This project use only points() and shadows(the colors) in its rendering, the algorithm randoms sorts to 5000-9000 points for each iteration. So rendering time can take a while depending of ammount of points the algo has sorted. 
Can take from 30 seconds to 1 minute to full render, after it the textures are instantly applied.

// 5 Shadow Colors
// 5 Background Colors


Works properly on Chromium based Web Browsers.






-Press "S" to save a .png file of the artwork


This is a project in p5.js



Omar Lobato,
08/03/2022.
